# CODEOWNERS Template for agentic-dev-framework Adopters

# The Review Council identifies which agents are relevant to a change.
# Map agent domains to human reviewers using CODEOWNERS so that council
# findings are reviewed by the humans most qualified to evaluate them.
#
# Usage:
#   1. Copy this file to .github/CODEOWNERS in your project.
#   2. Replace placeholder team names (@security-team, @frontend-team, etc.)
#      with your organization's actual GitHub teams or usernames.
#   3. Remove sections that don't apply to your project type.
#   4. Add project-specific paths as needed.
#
# GitHub CODEOWNERS rules:
#   - Last matching pattern wins.
#   - Use @org/team-name for GitHub teams, @username for individuals.
#   - Patterns follow .gitignore syntax.
#
# Framework agent → reviewer mapping rationale:
#   Guardian perspective (security findings) → @security-team
#   Bold UX Designer + Accessibility → @frontend-team
#   DevOps/Infrastructure → @platform-team
#   Framework configuration → @platform-team (changes affect all agents)

# =============================================================================
# DEFAULT: All files require at least one review
# =============================================================================
*                                   @team-lead

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY-SENSITIVE PATHS
# Guardian perspective always runs here. Map to humans who can evaluate
# security findings (auth flows, input validation, middleware, migrations).
# =============================================================================
{{SERVER_SOURCE_DIR}}/auth/         @security-team
{{SERVER_SOURCE_DIR}}/middleware/   @security-team
**/migrations/                      @database-team @security-team
**/seeds/                           @database-team
**/.env.example                     @security-team

# =============================================================================
# FRONTEND / CLIENT
# UX Designer + Accessibility perspective. Map to humans who can review
# visual hierarchy, accessibility, and result discoverability findings.
# =============================================================================
{{CLIENT_SOURCE_DIR}}/              @frontend-team

# =============================================================================
# INFRASTRUCTURE
# DevOps/Infrastructure agent scope. Map to platform team or whoever
# owns container, CI/CD, and deployment configuration.
# =============================================================================
**/Dockerfile                       @platform-team
**/Dockerfile.*                     @platform-team
**/*.yml                            @platform-team
**/*.yaml                           @platform-team
.github/workflows/                  @platform-team
{{CONTAINER_COMPOSE_FILE}}          @platform-team @security-team

# =============================================================================
# FRAMEWORK CONFIGURATION
# Changes to agent definitions, skills, and instructions affect how the
# AI assistant behaves for the entire team. Require platform team review.
# =============================================================================
.github/agents/                     @platform-team
.github/instructions/               @platform-team
.github/skills/                     @platform-team
.github/prompts/                    @platform-team
docs/FRAMEWORK_PROFILE.md           @platform-team
TOKENS.md                           @platform-team

# =============================================================================
# COMPLIANCE AND AUDIT (Enterprise profile only)
# Audit records and ADRs are compliance evidence. Require a designated
# compliance reviewer or tech lead sign-off.
# =============================================================================
docs/audit/                         @compliance-reviewer @team-lead
docs/adr/                           @tech-lead @team-lead

# =============================================================================
# MONOREPO SERVICE BOUNDARIES (uncomment and customize if using monorepo)
# Each service should have its own owner team for cross-service change review.
# =============================================================================
# services/api/                     @api-team
# services/worker/                  @backend-team
# services/frontend/                @frontend-team
# shared/                           @platform-team @tech-lead
